      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profiles, fluid temperature, hematocrit, blood viscosity) must be measured and reported with uncertainty bounds for all validation operating points.",
      "rationale": "Experiments were performed under controlled laboratory conditions; however, inlet velocity profiles and hematocrit were not individually measured per test run. Nominal values assumed from literature, introducing unquantified input uncertainty."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative validation metric (e.g., validation uncertainty u_val) computed for hemolysis index at each operating point, accounting for experimental and numerical uncertainties.",
      "rationale": "Comparisons presented as percent-difference tables. Formal validation metric u_val not computed; experimental measurement uncertainty not propagated through comparison. Achieved level 2 against required level 4."
